# Always update production

When you finish a user-facing change (feature, fix, seed that affects prod demo data):

1. Commit the chunk (commit-as-you-go).
2. **Push to `main`** and **deploy with `npx vercel --prod --yes`** in the same turn — do not leave work only on localhost.
3. Confirm the deploy aliased to https://haven-pm.vercel.app (or report failure).
4. Only skip push/deploy if the user explicitly says not to publish, or the change is purely local tooling with no app impact.

Request approval when required for protected `main` / production deploy; do not stop after a local-only commit without attempting publish.
